      • strToDate

        public static java.util.Date strToDate(java.lang.String strDate)
        Converts a proper String representing a date arranged in the common order of the German-speaking area, e. g. 14.03.95 or 14.03.1995, to Date. Permitted as separators are white-space character, ., - and /.

        If there are given only two digits for year, the year is completed automatically according to the current century, yet so that the date is lying in the past. For example, xx.xx.99 becomes to xx.xx.1999.

        Parameters:
        strDate - the String which contains a Date
        Returns:
        the represented Date or null if the given String cannot be parsed

      • addJoke

        public void addJoke(Joke joke)
        Adds a new Joke to the list of recent jokes shown to this user.

        Only the last five jokes are stored. If the given joke is already existing in list, the existing one will be removed.
